  "reviewer_message": "RESULT \u2014 Growth-rate residual \u0394(z) carries NO functional signal.\n  \u2022 Dataset : Alestas+2022 Table II, N=63 points, z \u2208 [0.001, 1.944].\n  \u2022 GR baseline (\u03c3\u2088\u2080 free) : \u03c7\u00b2/dof = 0.430, \u03c3\u2088\u2080 = 0.7815 (Planck: 0.811).\n  \u2022 Best ADCD candidate : 'Constant offset' (BIC = 5.98);\n    null 1-param constant offset: BIC = 5.98.\n  \u2022 \u0394BIC vs null = +0.00 \u2192 the constant offset is preferred;\n    no z-dependent correction beats a pure amplitude renormalisation.\n  \u2022 Conclusion : the S\u2088 tension in f\u03c3\u2088 is NOT an ADCD-discoverable\n    functional anomaly on this dataset \u2014 it is fully absorbed by a\n    single nuisance parameter (\u03c3\u2088\u2080). The wide-binary verdict (ADCDD\n    \u2261 Simple MOND, does not win there either) is reinforced: ADCD does\n    not surface a novel functional correction in growth-rate data.",
